00040    * Read parameters speciesId, nRegrow, and nTrial
00041    */
00042    void CfbHomoReptationMove::readParam(std::istream& in) 
00043    {
00044       // Read parameters
00045       readProbability(in);
00046       read<int>(in, "speciesId", speciesId_);
00047       read<int>(in, "nTrial", nTrial_);
00048 
00049       // Check that 0 < nTrial_ <= MaxTrial
00050       if (nTrial_ <=0 || nTrial_ > MaxTrial_) {
00051          UTIL_THROW("Invalid value input for nTrial");
00052       }
00053 
00054       // Check that the Species is actually a Homopolymer
00055       Homopolymer* speciesPtr;
00056       speciesPtr = dynamic_cast<Homopolymer*>(&(simulation().species(speciesId_)));
00057       if (!speciesPtr) {
00058          UTIL_THROW("Attempted use of CfbHomoReptation with Species that is not a Homopolymer");
00059       }
00060   
00061    }

00063    /* 
00064    * Generate, attempt and accept or reject a Monte Carlo move.
00065    */
00066    bool CfbHomoReptationMove::move() 
00067    {
00068       Vector    oldPos, newPos;
00069       double    rosen_r,  rosen_f;
00070       double    energy_r, energy_f;
00071       Atom     *tailPtr; // pointer to the tail atom (to be removed)
00072       Atom     *atomPtr; // resetable atom pointer
00073       Molecule *molPtr;  // pointer to randomly chosen molecule
00074       int       length, sign, headId, tailId, bondType, i;
00075       bool      accept;
00076      
00077       incrementNAttempt();
00078 
00079       // Choose a molecule at random
00080       molPtr = &(system().randomMolecule(speciesId_));
00081       length = molPtr->nAtom();
00082 
00083       // Choose which chain end to regrow
00084       if (random().uniform(0.0, 1.0) > 0.5) {
00085          sign = +1;
00086          headId = length - 1;
00087          tailId = 0;
00088       } else {
00089          sign = -1;
00090          headId = 0;
00091          tailId = length - 1;
00092       }
00093 
00094       // Store current positions of tail
00095       oldPos = molPtr->atom(tailId).position();
00096    
00097       // Delete tail monomers
00098       tailPtr = &(molPtr->atom(tailId));
00099       atomPtr = tailPtr + sign;
00100       if (sign == 1) {
00101          bondType = molPtr->bond(0).typeId();
00102       } else {
00103          bondType = molPtr->bond(length-2).typeId();
00104       }
00105       deleteEndAtom(tailPtr, atomPtr, bondType, rosen_r, energy_r);
00106 
00107       #ifndef INTER_NOPAIR
00108       // Delete from McSystem cell list
00109       system().pairPotential().deleteAtom(*tailPtr);
00110       #endif
00111    
00112       // Regrow head, using tailPtr to store properties of the new head.
00113       atomPtr = &(molPtr->atom(headId));
00114       tailPtr->setTypeId(atomPtr->typeId());
00115       tailPtr->mask().clear();
00116       #ifndef MCMD_NOMASKBONDED
00117       tailPtr->mask().append(*atomPtr);
00118       #endif
00119       if (sign == 1) {
00120          bondType = molPtr->bond(length-2).typeId();
00121       } else {
00122          bondType = molPtr->bond(0).typeId();
00123       }
00124       addEndAtom(tailPtr, atomPtr, bondType, rosen_f, energy_f);
00125 
00126       // Restore original type and connectivity of tail Atom
00127       atomPtr = tailPtr + sign;
00128       tailPtr->setTypeId(atomPtr->typeId());
00129       tailPtr->mask().clear();
00130       #ifndef MCMD_NOMASKBONDED
00131       tailPtr->mask().append(*atomPtr);
00132       #endif
00133 
00134       // Decide whether to accept or reject
00135       accept = random().metropolis(rosen_f/rosen_r);
00136       if (accept) {
00137 
00138          // Increment nAccept, the number accepted moves.
00139          incrementNAccept();
00140 
00141          // Store new head position
00142          newPos = tailPtr->position();
00143    
00144          tailPtr->position() = atomPtr->position();
00145 
00146          #ifndef INTER_NOPAIR
00147          // Add back to system cell list
00148          system().pairPotential().addAtom(*tailPtr);
00149          #endif
00150    
00151          // Shift atom positions towards the head
00152          for (i=1; i < length - 1; ++i) {
00153             //system().moveAtom(*atomPtr, (atomPtr+sign)->position());
00154             atomPtr->position() = (atomPtr+sign)->position();
00155             #ifndef INTER_NOPAIR
00156             system().pairPotential().updateAtomCell(*atomPtr);
00157             #endif
00158             atomPtr += sign;
00159          }
00160    
00161          // Move head atom to new chosen position
00162          //system().moveAtom(*atomPtr, newPos);
00163          atomPtr->position() = newPos;
00164          #ifndef INTER_NOPAIR
00165          system().pairPotential().updateAtomCell(*atomPtr);
00166          #endif
00167 
00168       } else {
00169 
00170          // Restore old position of tail
00171          tailPtr->position() = oldPos;
00172 
00173          #ifndef INTER_NOPAIR
00174          // Add tail back to System cell list.
00175          system().pairPotential().addAtom(*tailPtr);
00176          #endif
00177    
00178       }
00179 
00180       return accept;
00181    
00182    }
